# Local Actions (lic)

When GitHub Actions is unavailable or out of minutes:

```bash
./scripts/local-ci.sh           # native
./scripts/local-ci.sh --docker  # Ubuntu 24.04 parity with GHA
```

From **benchmarks** sibling repo:

```bash
./scripts/run-local-actions.sh lic
python3 scripts/local-ci-sweep.py --repo lic --pr N
```

Merge gate in benchmarks reads `data/latest/local-ci-results.json`. Do not merge without GHA green **or** a fresh local-ci pass.

See also `../benchmarks/.cursor/rules/li-local-actions-quota.mdc` when both repos are checked out.
